                     <interp inst="t18210718-58-person572" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a surgeon in the Westminster Infirmary; the deceased was brought there on Monday, the 18th, between eight and nine o'clock at night - I examined his head, he had a wound over the right eyebrow, about two inches and a half in breadth, from the parts separating - I found the scull fractured, the broken pieces of bone pressed on the brain; he died on the following Friday; the fracture of the scull was the cause of his death.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. BROADRICK. Q. Could you say what had caused the cut - A. I cannot say; any sharp-edged instrument might have done it, a sword would do it.</p>
               <p>MR. 
               <persName id="t18210718-58-person573">
                  ANTHONY 
                  WHITE
               <interp inst="t18210718-58-person573" type="surname" value="WHITE"></interp>
