                     <interp inst="t18210718-58-person575" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a corporal in the Coldstream Guards. On the evening of the 18th of June, I came by the Almonry about seven o'clock, heard a disturbance there, and saw a soldier with his jacket off, and about twenty more soldiers, and about a hundred persons altogether - I did not know the soldier with his jacket off - Serjeant Child was with me; we dispersed the mob as well as we could - the prisoner, Jones, took the soldier, who<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182107180031"></xptr>was without a jacket, away; the mob ran, and the soldiers dispersed.</p>
               <p>MR. ANDREWS. Q. What is the latest time you saw Jones - A. About half-past seven o'clock.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210718-58-person576">
