               <p>"There is a row with some of your men." We went into the Almonry and saw two men, one was in a soldier's dress with his jacket in his hand - I suppose there might be twenty or thirty soldiers together; I was pressing the soldier to put his jacket on and go home - I was followed by the prisoner Jones and another man; Jones assisted me in dispersing the soldiers, he was sober.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210718-58-person578">
